{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":73014,"duration_api_ms":72518,"num_turns":19,"result":"The fix is complete and minimal. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Bug**: The `JaccardDistance.dist` method in `sklearn/neighbors/dist_metrics.pyx` performed a division by `nnz` (number of non-zero dimensions) without checking if `nnz` is zero. When two all-zero vectors are compared, `nnz` is 0, causing a division by zero.\n\n**Fix**: Added a guard `if nnz == 0: return 0.0` before the division. This ensures that when both vectors are all zeros (they are identical), the Jaccard distance correctly returns 0.0, which satisfies the identity property of a distance metric: d(x, x) = 0.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a512a382-bdb2-4570-8355-27db8eda00bc","total_cost_usd":0.41304765,"usage":{"input_tokens":113223,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1003,"cache_read_input_tokens":52008,"output_tokens":3601,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_deleted_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed":{"inputTokens":113223,"outputTokens":3601,"cacheReadInputTokens":52008,"cacheCreationInputTokens":1003,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.41304765,"contextWindow":196000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"86836fd5-8749-4830-bf76-f0451bf155b7"}
